snippet.textDisplay:
I LOVED this game. My favorite Silent Hill ever, and my favorite horror game ever. It's also the first horror game I ever played, unless you count Uninvited on the NES, which was in a different genre but still horror themed. 

So many people talk about how great SH2 is, but I never cared for it. I loved SH3's setting, main character, style of horror, everything.

snippet.textDisplay: I remember playing this on my trip to Mexico years ago. At night was very dark, sure there were street lights but the gap between two of them were kinda like a block away sometimes even farther. And even then there were some areas of the small town that would actually not have any at all. My fav. time that night was when I stopped at the very entrance of the town and in the far distance was 1 streetlight allalone and beyond that there was nothing butdarkness.I loved it but immediately felt fear.

snippet.textDisplay: Even after 10 years, I personally think this is the best surival horror game in terms of audiovisual presentation. My favorite SH soundtrack by Yamaoka and unmatched rusty visuals that still look nice today. Team Silent had such a unique and great vision of horror and fear, I'm still mad at Konami for disbanding them. There's a Silent Hill 3 making of video floating around on YouTube, if you're a fan of the series you should check it out, it's very interesting!
